23 /**
24 @file
25 Definitions of all server's session or global variables.
26
27 How to add new variables:
28
29 1. copy one of the existing variables, and edit the declaration.
30 2. if you need special behavior on assignment or additional checks
31 use ON_CHECK and ON_UPDATE callbacks.
32 3. *Don't* add new Sys_var classes or uncle Occam will come
33 with his razor to haunt you at nights
34
35 Note - all storage engine variables (for example myisam_whatever)
36 should go into the corresponding storage engine sources
37 (for example in storage/myisam/ha_myisam.cc) !
38 */
39

167 /**
168 We must have room for at least 400 table definitions in the table
169 cache, since otherwise there is no chance prepared
170 statements that use these many tables can work.
171 Prepared statements use table definition cache ids (table_map_id)
172 as table version identifiers. If the table definition
173 cache size is less than the number of tables used in a statement,
174 the contents of the table definition cache is guaranteed to rotate
175 between a prepare and execute. This leads to stable validation
176 errors. In future we shall use more stable version identifiers,
177 for now the only solution is to ensure that the table definition
178 cache can contain at least all tables of a given statement.
179 */
180 static constexpr const unsigned long TABLE_DEF_CACHE_MIN{400};
181 static constexpr const unsigned long SCHEMA_DEF_CACHE_MIN{256};
182 static constexpr const unsigned long STORED_PROGRAM_DEF_CACHE_MIN{256};
183 static constexpr const unsigned long TABLESPACE_DEF_CACHE_MIN{256};
184 /*
185 Default time to wait before aborting a new client connection
186 that does not respond to "initial server greeting" timely
187 */
188 static constexpr const unsigned long CONNECT_TIMEOUT{10};
189
190 /* Defaults for deprecated "insert delayed" */
191 static constexpr const unsigned long DELAYED_LIMIT{100};
192 static constexpr const unsigned long DELAYED_QUEUE_SIZE{1000};
193 static constexpr const unsigned long DELAYED_WAIT_TIMEOUT{5 * 60};

855 /**
856 Variable performance_schema_max_statement_classes.
857 The default number of statement classes is the sum of:
858 - COM_END for all regular "statement/com/...",
859 - 1 for "statement/com/new_packet", for unknown enum_server_command
860 - 1 for "statement/com/Error", for invalid enum_server_command
861 - SQLCOM_END for all regular "statement/sql/...",
862 - 1 for "statement/sql/error", for invalid enum_sql_command.
863 - SP_PSI_STATEMENT_INFO_COUNT for "statement/sp/...".
864 - CLONE_PSI_STATEMENT_COUNT for "statement/clone/...".
865 - 1 for "statement/rpl/relay_log", for replicated statements.
866 - 1 for "statement/scheduler/event", for scheduled events.
867 */
868 static Sys_var_ulong Sys_pfs_max_statement_classes(
869 "performance_schema_max_statement_classes",
870 "Maximum number of statement instruments.",
871 READ_ONLY GLOBAL_VAR(pfs_param.m_statement_class_sizing),
872 CMD_LINE(REQUIRED_ARG), VALID_RANGE(0, 256),
873 DEFAULT((ulong)SQLCOM_END + (ulong)COM_END + 5 +
874 SP_PSI_STATEMENT_INFO_COUNT + CLONE_PSI_STATEMENT_COUNT),
875 BLOCK_SIZE(1), PFS_TRAILING_PROPERTIES);
876

939 static Sys_var_ulong Sys_pfs_max_digest_sample_age(
940 "performance_schema_max_digest_sample_age",

2702 enum_var_type type [[maybe_unused]]) {
2703 64 bool ret = false;
2704 // syntax is OK and services exist; try to initialize them!

✗ Branch 1 not taken.

2710
1/2
✗ Branch 0 not taken.
✓ Branch 1 taken 64 times.
 64 if (pipeline_config == nullptr) return true;
2711
2712 /*
2713 Temporarily release mutex.
2714 This solves two issues:
2715
2716 a) Setting up the error-logger may implicitly load external
2717 logging components. The init-function of such a component
2718 may try to install a system-variable and then ask the system
2719 for a (persisted / passed on the command-line / ...) initial
2720 value for said variable. The function in the component framework
2721 that tries to obtain this value tries to obtain the mutex
2722 LOCK_global_system_variables.
2723
2724 Note that implicit loading is attempted during the pre-check
2725 phase and thus should already have happened at this stage
2726 and no longer be a concern.
2727
2728 b) This function is called with the mutex held.
2729 log_builtins_error_stack() will obtain an exclusive lock on
2730 THR_LOCK_log_stack while it re-configures the error-logger.
2731 A different session might run FLUSH ERROR LOGS at the same time.
2732 This obtains THR_LOCK_log_stack first; an individual component's
2733 flush function might then try to re-install its system-variables
2734 on flush, which would try to obtain LOCK_global_system_variables
2735 as per above. I.e. both functions would try to obtain the two
2736 locks in a different order.
2737
2738 Note that components should not behave that way; they should
2739 install/uninstall their variables on init/exit, not on open/close.
2740
2741 Both issues are admittedly unlikely, but guarding against them is cheap.
2742 */
2743
1/2
✓ Branch 0 taken 64 times.
✗ Branch 1 not taken.
 64 mysql_mutex_unlock(&LOCK_global_system_variables);
2744
2745
2/4
✓ Branch 0 taken 64 times.
✗ Branch 1 not taken.
✗ Branch 2 not taken.
✓ Branch 3 taken 64 times.

2746 ✗ if (pos < strlen(pipeline_config)) /* purecov: begin inspected */

2748 ER_CANT_START_ERROR_LOG_SERVICE,
2749 ER_THD(thd, ER_CANT_START_ERROR_LOG_SERVICE),

 1196 !(thd->in_active_multi_stmt_transaction() || thd->in_sub_stmt)) {
5463 /*
5464 Update the isolation level of the next transaction.
5465 I.e. if one did:
5466 COMMIT;
5467 SET SESSION ISOLATION LEVEL ...
5468 BEGIN; <-- this transaction has the new isolation
5469 Note, that in case of:
5470 COMMIT;
5471 SET TRANSACTION ISOLATION LEVEL ...
5472 SET SESSION ISOLATION LEVEL ...
5473 BEGIN; <-- the session isolation level is used, not the
5474 result of SET TRANSACTION statement.
5475
5476 When we are in a trigger/function the transaction is already
5477 started. Adhering to above behavior, the SET TRANSACTION would
5478 fail when run from within trigger/function. And SET SESSION
5479 TRANSACTION would always succeed making the characteristics
5480 effective for the next transaction that starts.

5972 /*
5973 insert_id should *not* be marked as written to the binlog (i.e., it
5974 should *not* be IN_BINLOG), because we want any statement that
5975 refers to insert_id explicitly to be unsafe. (By "explicitly", we
5976 mean using @@session.insert_id, whereas insert_id is used
5977 "implicitly" when NULL value is inserted into an auto_increment
5978 column).
5979
5980 We want statements referring explicitly to @@session.insert_id to be
5981 unsafe, because insert_id is modified internally by the slave sql
5982 thread when NULL values are inserted in an AUTO_INCREMENT column.
5983 This modification interfers with the value of the
5984 @@session.insert_id variable if @@session.insert_id is referred
5985 explicitly by an insert statement (as is seen by executing "SET
5986 @@session.insert_id=0; CREATE TABLE t (a INT, b INT KEY
5987 AUTO_INCREMENT); INSERT INTO t(a) VALUES (@@session.insert_id);" in
5988 statement-based logging mode: t will be different on master and
5989 slave).
5990 */

7312 static Sys_var_gtid_mode Sys_gtid_mode(
7313 "gtid_mode",
7314 "Controls whether Global Transaction Identifiers (GTIDs) are "
7315 "enabled. Can be OFF, OFF_PERMISSIVE, ON_PERMISSIVE, or ON. OFF "
7316 "means that no transaction has a GTID. OFF_PERMISSIVE means that "
7317 "new transactions (committed in a client session using "
7318 "GTID_NEXT='AUTOMATIC') are not assigned any GTID, and "
7319 "replicated transactions are allowed to have or not have a "
7320 "GTID. ON_PERMISSIVE means that new transactions are assigned a "
7321 "GTID, and replicated transactions are allowed to have or not "
7322 "have a GTID. ON means that all transactions have a GTID. "
7323 "ON is required on a source before any replica can use "
7324 "SOURCE_AUTO_POSITION=1. To safely switch from OFF to ON, first "
7325 "set all servers to OFF_PERMISSIVE, then set all servers to "
7326 "ON_PERMISSIVE, then wait for all transactions without a GTID to "
7327 "be replicated and executed on all servers, and finally set all "
7328 "servers to GTID_MODE = ON.",
7329 PERSIST_AS_READONLY GLOBAL_VAR(Gtid_mode::sysvar_mode),

7335 "gtid_executed_compression_period",
7336 "Compress the mysql.gtid_executed table whenever this number of "
7337 "transactions have been added, by waking up a foreground thread "
7338 "(compress_gtid_table). This compression method only operates when "
7339 "binary logging is disabled on the replica; if binary logging is "
7340 "enabled, the table is compressed every time the binary log is "
7341 "rotated, and this value is ignored. Before MySQL 8.0.23, the "
7342 "default is 1000, and from MySQL 8.0.23, the default is zero, which "
7343 "disables this compression method. This is because in releases from "

7755
7756 /**
7757 Cost threshold for executing queries in a secondary storage engine. Only
7758 queries that have an estimated cost above this value will be attempted
7759 executed in a secondary storage engine.
7760
7761 Secondary storage engines are meant to accelerate queries that would otherwise
7762 take a relatively long time to execute. If a secondary storage engine accepts
7763 a query, it is assumed that it will be able to accelerate it. However, if the
7764 estimated cost of the query is low, the query will execute fast in the primary
7765 engine too, so there is little to gain by offloading the query to the
7766 secondary engine.
7767
7768 The default value aims to avoid use of secondary storage engines for queries
7769 that could be executed by the primary engine in a few tenths of seconds or
7770 less, and attempt to use secondary storage engines for queries would take
7771 seconds or more.
7772 */
7773 static Sys_var_double Sys_secondary_engine_cost_threshold(
7774 "secondary_engine_cost_threshold",
7775 "Controls which statements to consider for execution in a secondary "
7776 "storage engine. Only statements that have a cost estimate higher than "
7777 "this value will be attempted executed in a secondary storage engine.",
7778 HINT_UPDATEABLE SESSION_VAR(secondary_engine_cost_threshold),
7779 CMD_LINE(OPT_ARG), VALID_RANGE(0, DBL_MAX), DEFAULT(100000), NO_MUTEX_GUARD,
7780 NOT_IN_BINLOG, ON_CHECK(nullptr), ON_UPDATE(nullptr));
